00:14:39.940 --> 00:14:41.140
And I said yes, please.

240
00:14:41.140 --> 00:14:42.820
So they pulled the curtain back.

241
00:14:42.820 --> 00:14:45.500
So this person had access to all the light they needed,

242
00:14:45.500 --> 00:14:47.380
but they wanted to sit in darkness.

243
00:14:47.380 --> 00:14:49.820
Well here we're seeing like you are light in the world.

244
00:14:49.820 --> 00:14:54.260
So draw back the curtain.

245
00:14:54.300 --> 00:14:59.780
And walk in the light that is yours in Jesus.

246
00:14:59.780 --> 00:15:04.580
If His holy presence is with us and guiding us, then we should follow Him.

247
00:15:04.580 --> 00:15:07.180
It's interesting that the language of family is also used here.

248
00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:10.740
You know, that's how we started back at the start of chapter five,

249
00:15:10.740 --> 00:15:13.980
speaking of us as children of God, beloved children of God.

250
00:15:13.980 --> 00:15:16.500
And now it says that we are children of light.

251
00:15:16.500 --> 00:15:19.140
So if God is light, then His children are light.

252
00:15:19.140 --> 00:15:25.300
So something of His likeness should be reflected in us.

253
00:15:25.300 --> 00:15:26.660
All right, so this is put before us here.

254
00:15:26.660 --> 00:15:33.300
What it means to walk in the light by showing us the contrast between darkness and light.

255
00:15:33.300 --> 00:15:39.260
There's a, this walking in darkness is a total contradiction with our new identity.

256
00:15:39.260 --> 00:15:45.900
But walking in the light corresponds with this new identity if we are light.

257
00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:49.060
And he wants us to see both of them clearly here.

258
00:15:49.060 --> 00:15:53.020
So first of all, let's look at the unfruitful works of darkness.

259
00:15:53.020 --> 00:15:54.980
We're going to know what it means to walk in the light.

260
00:15:54.980 --> 00:15:59.700
What it will mean knowing what darkness is and having the light of God shining on that darkness

261
00:15:59.700 --> 00:16:02.860
to expose it for what it is.

262
00:16:02.860 --> 00:16:07.860
So it talks about things being out of place for children of light.

263
00:16:07.860 --> 00:16:11.060
So if you notice in chapter five and verse three,

264
00:16:11.060 --> 00:16:16.700
it talks about things that are not proper among saints.

265
00:16:16.740 --> 00:16:22.940
So don't think of that word proper as like proper table etiquette and like a fancy meal or something like that.

266
00:16:22.940 --> 00:16:26.140
Well, what that essentially means is there's things that don't fit.

267
00:16:26.140 --> 00:16:28.140
That's what the word means.

268
00:16:28.140 --> 00:16:30.740
It's like, you know, trying to crank your car with a house key.

269
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:32.820
Like it's just, it's just not going to work.

270
00:16:32.820 --> 00:16:37.860
They don't go together.

271
00:16:37.860 --> 00:16:41.780
It also talks about things not being named among God's people.

272
00:16:41.780 --> 00:16:44.620
And it's not saying they should be kept quiet.

273
00:16:44.660 --> 00:16:47.620
It's just saying they have no place whatsoever.

274
00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:51.540
They don't fit to the degree that there's zero place for it.

275
00:16:51.540 --> 00:16:55.900
You know, it's like if somebody has a peanut allergy, it's not like, oh, there was just one peanut there.

276
00:16:55.900 --> 00:16:59.340
Like, like if it's serious, it's serious.

277
00:16:59.340 --> 00:17:01.660
Like there's no place for it.

278
00:17:01.660 --> 00:17:03.780
And they give some specific examples.

279
00:17:03.780 --> 00:17:07.980
So let's go through the specific examples he gives just like he did in chapter four.

280
00:17:07.980 --> 00:17:09.620
He does here.

281
00:17:09.620 --> 00:17:14.580
So in verse three starts off by talking about sexual immorality and all impurity.

282
00:17:14.580 --> 00:17:17.460
So what is sexual immorality?

283
00:17:17.460 --> 00:17:26.020
What's any sexual activity that is outside the marriage covenant between a man and a woman?

284
00:17:26.020 --> 00:17:34.460
Then impurity is a broader category of lust that includes all kinds of lust.

285
00:17:34.460 --> 00:17:38.100
So just to be clear, God is not against sex.

286
00:17:38.100 --> 00:17:42.700
He created it as a good gift, but it is reserved for the context of marriage.

287
00:17:42.700 --> 00:17:45.940
That's what it is for.

288
00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:53.420
And so as Paul is writing this, he's writing this to people where they're in a society, in a culture where promiscuity was fairly common.

289
00:17:53.420 --> 00:17:58.380
And it was even part of religious practices in their day.

290
00:17:58.380 --> 00:18:05.780
And if they were going to be God's holy people, they were not to take part in that, however cultural it was.

291
00:18:05.780 --> 00:18:11.980
Now things may look different in our day than they did in the day in which Ephesians was written.

292
00:18:11.980 --> 00:18:19.380
But I don't think any of us would deny that this is a major thing in our culture today as well.

293
00:18:19.380 --> 00:18:21.180
It is an issue.

294
00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:31.100
We're in a culture where it seems that we're moving in a direction where just about anything goes as long as it is between consenting adults.

295
00:18:31.100 --> 00:18:38.940
But this is here once again, not to just critique our culture, but to see that these things can creep into the church as well.

296
00:18:38.940 --> 00:18:50.300
It can be in the form of outright affirming sexual immorality or keeping it hidden away, like not talking about it.

297
00:18:50.300 --> 00:18:58.700
Actually the word used for sexual immorality here is porneia, which is where we get our word pornography.

298
00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:08.460
While the use of porn is not an accepted practice in the church, it is all too common in people's private lives.

299
00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:12.060
And it needs to be brought into the light.

300
00:19:12.060 --> 00:19:15.740
It needs to be seen for what it is.

301
00:19:15.740 --> 00:19:17.700
Sexual immorality.

302
00:19:17.700 --> 00:19:23.620
But it also speaks of covetousness, covetousness or greed.

303
00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:25.220
That must not be named either.

304
00:19:25.220 --> 00:19:27.180
So what is covetousness?

305
00:19:27.180 --> 00:19:31.340
Well, it's the unrestrained desire for more.

306
00:19:31.340 --> 00:19:36.620
It's like feeling like I don't have enough and I've got to have something beyond what I already have.

307
00:19:36.620 --> 00:19:41.900
And the thing is, like you can talk about greed and people think, well, that just doesn't apply to me.

308
00:19:41.900 --> 00:19:50.100
I think the reason that is is because in our, we live in a materialistic culture and we think that we don't struggle with this because it is so pervasive.

309
00:19:50.100 --> 00:19:53.860
It is the waters that we are swimming in, in the West.

310
00:19:53.860 --> 00:20:02.100
One commentator described this as the great, unconfessed sin of the Western middle classes.

311
00:20:02.100 --> 00:20:05.100
It can take all different forms.

312
00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:14.260
It can take the form of excessive spending where we feel like we've got to have the best or the latest or the newest or whatever.

313
00:20:14.260 --> 00:20:19.340
We have a craving and we think that that will satisfy that particular craving.

314
00:20:19.340 --> 00:20:24.300
So it fills our thoughts, the thing that we want to get.

315
00:20:24.300 --> 00:20:27.940
But another way this can happen is more hidden.

316
00:20:27.940 --> 00:20:34.900
It can take the form of like hoarding to satisfy our longing for security.

317
00:20:34.900 --> 00:20:37.380
And that even feels like responsible.

318
00:20:37.380 --> 00:20:39.140
It's like responsible covetousness.

319
00:20:39.140 --> 00:20:41.980
Like I've got to have more in the stockpile.

320
00:20:41.980 --> 00:20:49.020
So there's that the kind of outward lavishness, but there's also the hidden security.

321
00:20:49.020 --> 00:20:56.820
It's fascinating that sexual sins have a stigma attached to them, you know, in evangelical churches.

322
00:20:56.820 --> 00:21:06.100
But excessive indulgence in these areas or that kind of hoarding mentality is not seen as a big deal, but it is.

323
00:21:06.100 --> 00:21:12.660
He even says here that those who are covetous are verse five idolaters.

324
00:21:12.660 --> 00:21:15.820
Covetousness is described as idolatry.

325
00:21:15.820 --> 00:21:21.660
And this puts its finger when he calls it idolatry both on sexual immorality and covetousness.

326
00:21:21.660 --> 00:21:26.620
Because if you look at the 10 commandments, the 10th commandment is do not covet.

327
00:21:26.620 --> 00:21:29.260
And one of the things is like do not covet your neighbor's wife.

328
00:21:29.260 --> 00:21:30.700
And it goes on to list other things.

329
00:21:30.700 --> 00:21:36.740
Right. So this is an all-encompassing thing for not being satisfied with what you have.

330
00:21:36.740 --> 00:21:43.660
Okay. And it puts its finger on the issue because the big issue here is what are you worshiping?

331
00:21:43.660 --> 00:21:46.300
What are we worshiping?

332
00:21:46.300 --> 00:21:48.140
Are we devoted to God?

333
00:21:48.140 --> 00:21:51.780
Are we devoted to our desires for other things?

334
00:21:51.780 --> 00:21:56.220
Are our thoughts filled with Him and His beauty and His glory?

335
00:21:56.220 --> 00:22:00.540
Or are they filled with something else?

336
00:22:00.540 --> 00:22:04.100
The question is also like, is He enough?

337
00:22:04.100 --> 00:22:10.540
Or do we feel we have to have these other things?

338
00:22:10.540 --> 00:22:15.820
Hebrews chapter 13 and verse five says, keep your life free from the love of money.

339
00:22:15.820 --> 00:22:18.780
And be content with what you have.

340
00:22:18.780 --> 00:22:20.060
Well, how can we do that?

341
00:22:20.060 --> 00:22:25.660
It then goes on to say, for He Himself, God Himself has said,

342
00:22:25.660 --> 00:22:32.340
I will never leave you or forsake you.

343
00:22:32.340 --> 00:22:35.900
He also moves on to talk about our speech.

344
00:22:35.900 --> 00:22:42.340
He says, let no verse four filthiness nor foolish talk nor crude joking.

345
00:22:42.340 --> 00:22:48.460
So course language or off-color humor is what is being referred to here.

346
00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:52.660
Talk about something that has become commonplace in our day, not just in private,

347
00:22:52.660 --> 00:22:56.820
but in public discourse as well.

348
00:22:56.820 --> 00:22:59.500
Things are excused as, oh, it's just locker room talk,

349
00:22:59.500 --> 00:23:02.620
as though that was an okay way to speak.

350
00:23:02.620 --> 00:23:06.300
That's just how people talk these days.

351
00:23:06.300 --> 00:23:13.700
This has no place in the speech of those who are children of light.

352
00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:20.220
Being edgy in our language does not promote grace.

353
00:23:20.220 --> 00:23:23.980
Jesus says, out of the abundance of the heart, the mouth speaks.

354
00:23:23.980 --> 00:23:26.500
He said that in Luke chapter six, verse 45.

355
00:23:26.500 --> 00:23:32.060
So our words are an indication of the condition of our hearts.

356
00:23:32.060 --> 00:23:36.340
And if we speak in these ways, it demonstrates that we really don't see sin

357
00:23:36.340 --> 00:23:43.540
as being as serious or as dangerous as it truly is.

358
00:23:43.540 --> 00:23:46.340
I read about someone who was on vacation.

359
00:23:46.340 --> 00:23:49.900
And while they were there, they saw this little snake on the beach.

360
00:23:49.900 --> 00:23:52.740
And they picked it up and they had some pictures with it.

361
00:23:52.740 --> 00:23:56.500
They even kissed the snake and had a nice time put it down.

362
00:23:56.500 --> 00:23:59.860
And they didn't find out until afterwards when they posted it online

363
00:23:59.860 --> 00:24:01.380
that that snake was a sea snake.

364
00:24:01.380 --> 00:24:04.700
That was 10 times as venomous as any rattlesnake.

365
00:24:04.700 --> 00:24:09.820
And so they literally had death in their hands, not realizing.

366
00:24:09.820 --> 00:24:12.540
So we see this here in the text.

367
00:24:12.540 --> 00:24:16.940
Paul is saying, this is what sin is and here is how serious it is.

368
00:24:16.940 --> 00:24:20.420
Here's how dangerous it is.

369
00:24:20.420 --> 00:24:24.260
Verse five, what does it say?

370
00:24:24.260 --> 00:24:27.540
He says, you may be sure of this that everyone who is sexually immoral or

371
00:24:27.580 --> 00:24:31.860
impure or who is covetous, that is an idolatry.

372
00:24:31.860 --> 00:24:33.500
Here's how serious it is.

373
00:24:33.500 --> 00:24:37.820
Has no inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and God.

374
00:24:41.060 --> 00:24:46.940
It also says, because of these things, the wrath of God comes upon

375
00:24:46.940 --> 00:24:49.220
the sons of disobedience.

376
00:24:51.380 --> 00:24:55.500
So the God who is lied is also a consuming fire, we read about in

377
00:24:55.540 --> 00:25:00.460
Deuteronomy chapter nine in verse three, fire destroys.

378
00:25:00.460 --> 00:25:03.860
It's also a picture of judgments.

379
00:25:03.860 --> 00:25:07.700
So people may try to deceive us into thinking these things are not really

380
00:25:07.700 --> 00:25:14.140
sinful or they may downplay God's judgments and they may even do so from a pulpit.

381
00:25:14.140 --> 00:25:18.620
Some may even celebrate sinful ways of life as freedom, but

382
00:25:18.620 --> 00:25:24.860
Scripture says, do not be deceived by their empty words.

383
00:25:24.900 --> 00:25:28.140
So you have this word of warning, those who practice these things will not inherit

384
00:25:28.140 --> 00:25:29.500
the kingdom.

385
00:25:29.500 --> 00:25:33.020
Instead, they will receive the wrath of God.

386
00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:37.740
But could also give a word of assurance here.

387
00:25:37.740 --> 00:25:40.100
Remember this is written to Christians.

388
00:25:40.100 --> 00:25:44.540
So if Christians need to be told to not practice these things,

389
00:25:44.540 --> 00:25:49.220
implicit in that is that we fail in these areas.

390
00:25:49.220 --> 00:25:49.860
We do sin.

391
00:25:50.860 --> 00:25:56.860
Those who do not enter the kingdom are those for whom this is a settled habitual

392
00:25:57.860 --> 00:25:58.860
practice.

393
00:25:58.860 --> 00:26:02.860
It's talking about a way of life that is habitual.

394
00:26:02.860 --> 00:26:06.860
So this is different to struggling with sin as a believer.

395
00:26:06.860 --> 00:26:10.860
So the point here is not that we don't fall or that we don't fail.

396
00:26:10.860 --> 00:26:12.860
We do, we will.

397
00:26:12.860 --> 00:26:16.860
But the difference is instead of keeping our sins hidden away in sin,

398
00:26:16.860 --> 00:26:20.860
the difference is instead of keeping our sins hidden away in the dark,

399
00:26:20.860 --> 00:26:24.860
we bring them out into the light.

400
00:26:24.860 --> 00:26:29.860
We confess our sins, 1 John 1 and verse 9 says, we confess our sins knowing that

401
00:26:29.860 --> 00:26:35.860
He is faithful and just to forgive us of our sins and to cleanse us from all

402
00:26:35.860 --> 00:26:37.860
unrighteousness.

403
00:26:37.860 --> 00:26:39.860
We don't hold on to them.

404
00:26:39.860 --> 00:26:44.860
Yes, we fail, but we go to war with our sin and we bring them into the light

405
00:26:44.860 --> 00:26:51.860
and we are Christ in confession and receiving His cleansing.

406
00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:56.860
But we also recognize as we do that that these ways of darkness do not correspond

407
00:26:56.860 --> 00:26:59.860
with being children of light.

408
00:26:59.860 --> 00:27:02.860
But there is a way that does correspond to that.

409
00:27:02.860 --> 00:27:05.860
He speaks not only of the fruit of the works of darkness,

410
00:27:05.860 --> 00:27:08.860
He speaks of the fruit of light here as well.

411
00:27:08.860 --> 00:27:12.860
You see that in verse 9, the fruit of light is found in all that is good

412
00:27:12.860 --> 00:27:15.860
and righteous and true.

413
00:27:15.860 --> 00:27:18.860
So this is not just about what we refuse.

414
00:27:18.860 --> 00:27:20.860
It's also about what we replace.

415
00:27:20.860 --> 00:27:22.860
So we're refusing the darkness.

416
00:27:22.860 --> 00:27:26.860
We see the danger of that, but we also see the goodness of what God has laid

417
00:27:26.860 --> 00:27:29.860
before us and we pursue those better things.

418
00:27:29.860 --> 00:27:32.860
So there's a positive motivation here.

419
00:27:32.860 --> 00:27:36.860
You see that in what He says about our speech in verse 4.

420
00:27:36.860 --> 00:27:40.860
So if you go back to that, so let's not have this filthiness or foolish talk

421
00:27:40.860 --> 00:27:44.860
or crude joking be part of our speech, but instead let there be what?

422
00:27:44.860 --> 00:27:46.860
Thanksgiving.

423
00:27:46.860 --> 00:27:51.860
So Thanksgiving is the opposite of desiring more than what you have been given.

424
00:27:51.860 --> 00:27:56.860
So someone who is giving thanks is someone who sees how amazing what they already have is.

425
00:27:56.860 --> 00:28:01.860
They see the grace of God and they give Him thanks for that.

426
00:28:01.860 --> 00:28:03.860
Right? So they're not just saying, I don't do that.

427
00:28:03.860 --> 00:28:05.860
I don't talk that way.

428
00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:09.860
They're saying something that's so much better than giving God thanks for it.

429
00:28:09.860 --> 00:28:17.860
So if we're walking in the light, we see and savor what God has already given us.

430
00:28:17.860 --> 00:28:19.860
Three quick things He's given us.

431
00:28:19.860 --> 00:28:22.860
Best of all, He's given us Himself.

432
00:28:22.860 --> 00:28:24.860
He is our exceeding joy.

433
00:28:24.860 --> 00:28:29.860
He is the one, the only one who can satisfy our hunger and our thirst.

434
00:28:29.860 --> 00:28:31.860
He fully satisfies.

435
00:28:31.860 --> 00:28:36.860
But He's also the God who gives us good things.

436
00:28:36.860 --> 00:28:39.860
Every good gift comes from Him.

437
00:28:39.860 --> 00:28:41.860
We read in James 1.

438
00:28:41.860 --> 00:28:47.860
So He helps us to appreciate and enjoy all of the good gifts He has given us.

439
00:28:47.860 --> 00:28:52.860
That can obviously mean we can and should enjoy spiritual things like our Bibles,

440
00:28:52.860 --> 00:29:00.860
but He also gives us a capacity to enjoy the material things that He has given us as well.

441
00:29:00.860 --> 00:29:03.860
Instead of craving the things that are beyond our reach,

442
00:29:03.860 --> 00:29:08.860
we really see what we have now and we enjoy it with a greater depth.

443
00:29:08.860 --> 00:29:10.860
And we give Him thanks.

444
00:29:10.860 --> 00:29:12.860
That could be our friendships.

445
00:29:12.860 --> 00:29:13.860
It could be our spouse.

446
00:29:13.860 --> 00:29:14.860
It could be our children.

447
00:29:14.860 --> 00:29:17.860
It could be things out in nature.

448
00:29:17.860 --> 00:29:19.860
Whatever it is for you,

449
00:29:19.860 --> 00:29:25.860
He helps us to see and enjoy beauty in the so-called ordinary.

450
00:29:25.860 --> 00:29:30.860
We see His glory reflected in what is before us.

451
00:29:30.860 --> 00:29:35.860
We also see the good that He's given us in His righteousness.

452
00:29:35.860 --> 00:29:39.860
So the fruit of light is seeking out what is good and right and true.

453
00:29:39.860 --> 00:29:46.860
It is seeing the beauty of holiness and seeking to live it out by God's grace.

454
00:29:46.860 --> 00:29:48.860
So walk in the light.

455
00:29:48.860 --> 00:29:53.860
But what happens when we as children of light walk in the light?

456
00:29:53.860 --> 00:29:54.860
So we are light.

457
00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:56.860
We walk in the light.

458
00:29:56.860 --> 00:29:57.860
Then what?

459
00:29:57.860 --> 00:30:04.860
The last thing I want to see is that we shine as light in the world.

460
00:30:04.860 --> 00:30:08.860
So light serves a purpose beyond shining.

461
00:30:08.860 --> 00:30:12.860
It guides as we've seen already.

462
00:30:12.860 --> 00:30:17.860
A few months ago, our family went out to Oak Mountain State Park

463
00:30:17.860 --> 00:30:18.860
and we went camping together.

464
00:30:18.860 --> 00:30:20.860
And it was great.

465
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:21.860
Really enjoyed it.

466
00:30:21.860 --> 00:30:22.860
And the year before we went,

467
00:30:22.860 --> 00:30:24.860
we had a little walk around the place.

468
00:30:24.860 --> 00:30:28.860
And I took the kids on a nighttime hike on a trail.

469
00:30:28.860 --> 00:30:30.860
And we had the flashlight out walking around.

470
00:30:30.860 --> 00:30:32.860
But this time we went and we took the flashlights.

471
00:30:32.860 --> 00:30:35.860
And all of a sudden we realized we didn't even need the flashlights

472
00:30:35.860 --> 00:30:38.860
because there was a full moon and it was so bright

473
00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:40.860
and it was reflecting off the water as well.

474
00:30:40.860 --> 00:30:43.860
We could walk through the trail because of the light that was reflected.

475
00:30:43.860 --> 00:30:45.860
The light that was reflected,

476
00:30:45.860 --> 00:30:47.860
the light of the sun reflected on the moon,

477
00:30:47.860 --> 00:30:51.860
gave us all that we need to show the way to go.

478
00:30:51.860 --> 00:30:55.860
It's God's desire that His people reflect His light,

479
00:30:55.860 --> 00:30:57.860
not just for themselves,

480
00:30:57.860 --> 00:31:02.860
but also so that others in the world may come to know Him as well.

481
00:31:02.860 --> 00:31:07.860
You see this in what He says to the people of Israel in Isaiah 49 and verse 6.

482
00:31:07.860 --> 00:31:08.860
He says,

483
00:31:08.860 --> 00:31:11.860
It is too light a thing that you should be my servant

484
00:31:11.860 --> 00:31:16.860
to raise up the tribes of Jacob and bring back the preserved of Israel.

485
00:31:16.860 --> 00:31:19.860
I will make you as a light for the nations

486
00:31:19.860 --> 00:31:23.860
that my salvation may reach to the end of the earth.

487
00:31:23.860 --> 00:31:28.860
You see this then in how Jesus describes His disciples.

488
00:31:28.860 --> 00:31:30.860
Matthew chapter 5 and verse 14,

489
00:31:30.860 --> 00:31:31.860
He says,

490
00:31:31.860 --> 00:31:34.860
You are the light of the world.

491
00:31:34.860 --> 00:31:35.860
He says,

492
00:31:35.860 --> 00:31:37.860
You're like a city set on a hill.

493
00:31:37.860 --> 00:31:39.860
You're like a lamp in a house.

494
00:31:39.860 --> 00:31:41.860
Like you don't hide the light.

495
00:31:41.860 --> 00:31:44.860
You let it show in the world

496
00:31:44.860 --> 00:31:48.860
that others may come to glorify your Father too.

497
00:31:48.860 --> 00:31:52.860
The apostle Peter speaks of the church as being the light.

498
00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:54.860
He talks about how God has made us His own,

499
00:31:54.860 --> 00:31:55.860
1 Peter 2.9,

500
00:31:55.860 --> 00:31:58.860
that you may proclaim the excellencies of Him

501
00:31:58.860 --> 00:32:01.860
who called you out of darkness

502
00:32:01.860 --> 00:32:04.860
and into His marvelous light.

503
00:32:04.860 --> 00:32:08.860
So God makes us lights so that we might make His salvation

504
00:32:08.860 --> 00:32:11.860
known to a world that is lost in darkness.

505
00:32:11.860 --> 00:32:15.860
We're not called to be partakers of the ways of the world,

506
00:32:15.860 --> 00:32:18.860
but we are called to be present in the world

507
00:32:18.860 --> 00:32:21.860
that they too might come to know Christ.

508
00:32:21.860 --> 00:32:24.860
But notice how it's drawn out in this text specifically.

509
00:32:24.860 --> 00:32:28.860
He talks about how light exposes the works of darkness.

510
00:32:28.860 --> 00:32:30.860
Verse 11 says,

511
00:32:30.860 --> 00:32:33.860
Take no part in the unfruitful works of darkness,

512
00:32:33.860 --> 00:32:37.860
but instead expose them.

513
00:32:37.860 --> 00:32:42.860
So turning on a light exposes what is hidden in the darkness.

514
00:32:42.860 --> 00:32:45.860
And if our lives are reflecting the light of Christ,

515
00:32:45.860 --> 00:32:48.860
it will expose the sinful ways of life

516
00:32:48.860 --> 00:32:52.860
that are hidden in darkness in the world.

517
00:32:52.860 --> 00:32:56.860
Now Paul doesn't specify as to how to go about this here,

518
00:32:56.860 --> 00:32:59.860
but you can see examples of this in Scripture

519
00:32:59.860 --> 00:33:02.860
of how this can happen both in word and deed.

520
00:33:02.860 --> 00:33:05.860
So our deeds can shine a light that exposes.

521
00:33:05.860 --> 00:33:08.860
So our lives should have such a distinct quality

522
00:33:08.860 --> 00:33:13.860
that it exposes the lostness of those that we are around.

523
00:33:13.860 --> 00:33:18.860
It's possible to be a joyful yet sometimes convicting presence

524
00:33:18.860 --> 00:33:21.860
merely by the way that you live around others

525
00:33:21.860 --> 00:33:24.860
who are living differently.

526
00:33:24.860 --> 00:33:27.860
The light can also come through in our words.

527
00:33:27.860 --> 00:33:30.860
There will be times when we are to speak

528
00:33:30.860 --> 00:33:35.860
in ways that expose the sin of the world.

529
00:33:35.860 --> 00:33:37.860
This is of course true societally.

530
00:33:37.860 --> 00:33:41.860
It does the church no favors to take a neutral middle ground stance

531
00:33:41.860 --> 00:33:44.860
on issues of clear right and wrong.

532
00:33:44.860 --> 00:33:47.860
And it's even worse when we do that with our own tribe,

533
00:33:47.860 --> 00:33:49.860
be it like a theological tribe or political tribe,

534
00:33:49.860 --> 00:33:54.860
as though we're perfect and only just calling out the sins of others.

535
00:33:54.860 --> 00:33:57.860
So we need to bring sin out into the light,

536
00:33:57.860 --> 00:33:59.860
but also personally in our conversation with somebody,

537
00:33:59.860 --> 00:34:03.860
it may be right sometimes to shed the light

538
00:34:03.860 --> 00:34:07.860
of God's word on what they are doing.

539
00:34:07.860 --> 00:34:09.860
It's sometimes right to look at someone in the eye

540
00:34:09.860 --> 00:34:12.860
and speak the truth about their sin to them.

541
00:34:12.860 --> 00:34:14.860
Now that doesn't mean you walk around the office

542
00:34:14.860 --> 00:34:17.860
like you're the moral police, you know, calling people out

543
00:34:17.860 --> 00:34:20.860
for anything to get wrong or something like that.

544
00:34:20.860 --> 00:34:22.860
That's not what it's saying here.

545
00:34:22.860 --> 00:34:25.860
But this does sometimes mean speaking clearly

546
00:34:25.860 --> 00:34:30.860
about the reality of sin and the coming judgments.

547
00:34:31.860 --> 00:34:33.860
We don't do this from a place of moral superiority,

548
00:34:33.860 --> 00:34:37.860
but from a place of love.

549
00:34:37.860 --> 00:34:39.860
So people need to know that they are lost

550
00:34:39.860 --> 00:34:41.860
if they're going to see the need to be saved.

551
00:34:41.860 --> 00:34:44.860
And if we're going to do that, we need to begin with ourselves,

552
00:34:44.860 --> 00:34:50.860
speaking of our own sin and our own need for the gospel.

553
00:34:50.860 --> 00:34:52.860
It's kind of like if you've got somebody who's lost

554
00:34:52.860 --> 00:34:54.860
out in the wilderness and somebody comes to find them

555
00:34:54.860 --> 00:34:57.860
with a flashlight and they find them,

556
00:34:57.860 --> 00:35:00.860
the light reveals, yes, their lostness,

557
00:35:00.860 --> 00:35:03.860
but it's also their salvation in it too.

558
00:35:03.860 --> 00:35:08.860
So we, yes, expose the sinfulness, the lostness of the world,

559
00:35:08.860 --> 00:35:12.860
but we do so that they might see the light of the gospel.

560
00:35:12.860 --> 00:35:15.860
So light leads to, it doesn't just expose,

561
00:35:15.860 --> 00:35:18.860
it leads to transformation and awakening.

562
00:35:18.860 --> 00:35:21.860
We want people to experience the transformation

563
00:35:21.860 --> 00:35:23.860
that we have experienced.

564
00:35:23.860 --> 00:35:26.860
So we see that in the start of verse 14.

565
00:35:26.860 --> 00:35:29.860
It says, for anything that becomes visible is light.

566
00:35:29.860 --> 00:35:33.860
So the hope is that when the light exposes the dire condition

567
00:35:33.860 --> 00:35:37.860
that people are in, that they will not retreat into the shadows,

568
00:35:37.860 --> 00:35:39.860
but remain in the light.

569
00:35:39.860 --> 00:35:44.860
And if they remain in the light, we see that they become light.

570
00:35:44.860 --> 00:35:47.860
This can be a bit confusing thinking about what this is saying here,

571
00:35:47.860 --> 00:35:52.860
but it seems to be pointing to a transformation, becoming light.

572
00:35:52.860 --> 00:35:56.860
So we long that people hear the gospel

573
00:35:56.860 --> 00:36:02.860
and they then confess their sins and then they move from being darkness

574
00:36:02.860 --> 00:36:06.860
to now being light in the Lord as we saw earlier.

575
00:36:06.860 --> 00:36:10.860
Then Paul goes on to quote something that's quite poetic.

576
00:36:10.860 --> 00:36:13.860
There at the end of verse 14, we'll end here.

577
00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:15.860
He says, this is therefore it says,

578
00:36:16.860 --> 00:36:21.860
This is likely an early hymn or confession.

579
00:36:21.860 --> 00:36:23.860
Some people think it was used at baptisms.

580
00:36:23.860 --> 00:36:24.860
I don't know.

581
00:36:24.860 --> 00:36:28.860
But it's essentially a mashup of different truths from Isaiah

582
00:36:28.860 --> 00:36:32.860
that points to the light of Jesus.

583
00:36:32.860 --> 00:36:33.860
Here's the idea.

584
00:36:33.860 --> 00:36:36.860
We are asleep, even dead in our sins.

585
00:36:36.860 --> 00:36:38.860
But then the light of Christ breaks through.

586
00:36:38.860 --> 00:36:39.860
We see his glory.

587
00:36:39.860 --> 00:36:41.860
We awake from slumber.

588
00:36:41.860 --> 00:36:43.860
We see the light of Christ.

589
00:36:43.860 --> 00:36:45.860
We see the light of glory.

590
00:36:45.860 --> 00:36:49.860
We awake from slumber and are given this new life in him.

591
00:36:49.860 --> 00:36:52.860
And in his light, we not only see who he is,

592
00:36:52.860 --> 00:36:56.860
we also see reality as it truly is.

593
00:36:56.860 --> 00:37:00.860
So we're calling out to people to wake up from their sleep,

594
00:37:00.860 --> 00:37:05.860
that the light of Christ might shine on them too.

595
00:37:05.860 --> 00:37:10.860
So we want to bring the light of the gospel to bear on our own lives

596
00:37:10.860 --> 00:37:13.860
and to give glory to those who are in heaven.

597
00:37:13.860 --> 00:37:16.860
And we want to bring the light of Christ to them too.

598
00:37:16.860 --> 00:37:18.860
So in the words of Jesus,

599
00:37:18.860 --> 00:37:20.860
let your light so shine before others

600
00:37:20.860 --> 00:37:22.860
that they may see your good works

601
00:37:22.860 --> 00:37:25.860
and give glory to your Father who is in heaven.

602
00:37:25.860 --> 00:37:26.860
Let's pray.

603
00:37:31.860 --> 00:37:34.860
Lord, you are light.

604
00:37:34.860 --> 00:37:38.860
And in you is no darkness.

605
00:37:38.860 --> 00:37:41.860
And in you is no fellowship with one another.

606
00:37:41.860 --> 00:37:46.860
And the blood of Jesus Christ cleanses us from all sin.

607
00:37:46.860 --> 00:37:50.860
And so Lord, I pray that you call us out from the shadows

608
00:37:50.860 --> 00:37:53.860
into your glorious light.

609
00:37:53.860 --> 00:37:57.860
Lord, we know that you expose us in our sin.

610
00:37:57.860 --> 00:38:00.860
Not that we might live in shame,

611
00:38:00.860 --> 00:38:05.860
but that we might receive cleansing in Jesus.

612
00:38:05.860 --> 00:38:12.860
That we would look away from our sinfulness even now to you.

613
00:38:12.860 --> 00:38:16.860
And we would behold your glory revealed in Jesus.

614
00:38:16.860 --> 00:38:21.860
Lord, help us to see how wonderful you are.

615
00:38:21.860 --> 00:38:24.860
And may we follow you as children of light.

616
00:38:24.860 --> 00:38:26.860
In Jesus' name, amen.

